# <type>(<optional scope>): <subject>
# |<---- Using a maximum of 72 characters ---->|
#
# Example types: build|chore|ci|docs|feat|fix|perf|refactor|style|test
#
# Format explanation:
# - type: what kind of change this is (required)
# - scope: what section of the codebase this change affects (optional)
# - subject: a short description of the change (required)
#
# Subject line imperatives:
# - Use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
# - Don't capitalize the first letter
# - No period (.) at the end
#
# Body (optional): |<---- Using a maximum of 100 characters per line ---->|
# - Explain the what and why (not how)
# - Can use multiple lines
# - Separate from subject with a blank line
#
# Footer (optional):
# - Can reference issues and pull requests
# - e.g., "Fixes #123", "Closes #456", "Related to #789"
#
# Breaking changes (if any):
# - Start with "BREAKING CHANGE:" and describe what changed and why
# - Or add ! after type/scope: "feat!:" or "feat(api)!:"
#
# Commitlint will enforce the format using these rules.
# See https://www.conventionalcommits.org/ for more details.
#
# Remember to remove all lines starting with # before committing.
